The assault case against Kwaito musician Mandla Maphumulo popularly known as “Mampintsha” is expected to resume at the Pinetown Magistrate’s Court on Wednesday. During the last court appearance Mampintsha was granted R2000 bail. He is facing a charge of assault with intent to cause grievous bodily harm. This after his girlfriend, Bongekile Simelane- popularly known as “Babes Wodumo”, released a live video on Instagram of an alleged attacked. During the last court appearance, Mampintsha laid counter assault charges against Simelane. Since the last court appearance the couple has been seen together at many events. Watch for more: 